Ask any farmer: Life is unpredictable. 
One thing we can do to ease that is give them certainty on policy. The RFS is the law of the land — we need to start acting like it, and put an end to these refinery exemptions and gap-year filings. Great points here from @RepDustyJohnson! https://t.co/5up95zaApC

full_text: I’m headed back to DC tonight to discuss postal issues. @SpeakerPelosi, you should keep members in DC until we come to a COVID-19 relief agreement for the American people. Congress can’t leave hurting Americans out to dry – let’s get to work on a bill that can pass the Senate.

1. Recruiting POC into LE
2. Maintenance & sharing of disciplinary records
3. Body cameras & their proper use
4. Records related to use of force & no-knock warrants
5. De-escalation training https://t.co/HjM7UtvIOG

Today, I joined my colleagues requesting swift financial support for America’s cattle ranchers impacted by #COVID19 

America’s cattle ranchers are playing a critical role in domestic food security which is why they need resources included in the CARES Act. 

READ THE LETTER ↓ https://t.co/gpFJC0VHIa

full_text: Like most of America, our #cattle producers are being impacted by the effects of the coronavirus. I’m proud to lead efforts to ensure they have a seat at the table and see the relief they so much deserve after dealing with volatile markets. https://t.co/XQGr5i4lPF

full_text: There were a number of provisions in today's appropriations bill I liked and fought for. Despite that fact, in the end, this agreement didn't do enough to address our nation's fiscal challenges. I voted no.

Israel’s Chief Rabbi told me that he periodically gets together with the leaders of the major Muslim, Jewish, Christian, and other Israeli faith groups. I asked him what they could agree on. His answer:

“The importance of families.” https://t.co/hIOaIT3mKf

Great to join Congressman @RepDustyJohnson in Davison County, SD last week as @Midcontinent starts building out high-speed Internet to 7,400 unserved locations.

full_text: Like the President, I’ve vehemently disagreed with the far left members of the House on policy, but his inappropriate comments were the wrong way to communicate that disagreement. We need to focus on governing this country, and his tweets weren’t helpful.

retweeted_text: Today I introduced the FEEDD Act with @RepDustyJohnson to give farmers flexibility to graze and harvest cover crops on prevent plant acres. Minnesota farmers need Congress to support bipartisan, common sense efforts like these - learn more here https://t.co/DljkDvdAq2

full_text: The #FEEDDact increases the use of cover crops on prevent plant acres to prevent soil erosion and enhance soil health. It would secure the overall farm safety net for diversified crop and livestock producers.

@ReynoldNesiba @Tony_Venhuizen @SDGovDaugaard Reynold, there is not a single member of Congress who is asking that work requirements be applied to children. 

The proposal:
- Able-bodied adults (18-50 yo), without dependents. 
- Work, training, volunteering, or education. 
- 20 hours a week.

My favorite comment from today’s hearing on food stamps:

“We talk too much about what our people can’t do, and not enough about what they can do.”

Work has dignity, and there is a job for almost everyone.

For the last decade, waste methane generated at the Sioux Falls Regional Landfill has been sent to Chancellor via an 11-mile pipeline. 

This morning we were happy to host @paultenhaken and @RepDustyJohnson for a signing ceremony to renew this partnership for another 10 years! https://t.co/y1a4a2Xors

full_text: Excited to celebrate the kind of proactive optimism this nation needs to drive growth. Congrats to @CitySiouxFalls and @POETbiofuels! https://t.co/lWbaJvWu9n

full_text:
I walked into work behind @RepRussFulcher this morn. Some members act like big shots. Not Russ. He was unassuming & kind, incl thanking officer for service. 

Russ didn’t know I was behind him. He was being nice because that’s who he is. 

You’ve got a good one, Idaho. Be proud.

Beginning Thursday, we are reopening ALL @usdafsa offices nationwide for a longer list of additional transactions during the partial government shutdown. Many thanks to FSA staff, dedicated to providing services to America's farmers. 

Key details here: https://t.co/D0TQrdO6gn https://t.co/cJ12Re51d2

full_text: 'Johnson said he’s made a point to talk to someone, whether they be from the White House, a Republican or a Democrat, on a daily basis about trying to find the common ground to potentially end the shutdown.' https://t.co/jsdC7JtFDl
